article.headline: Sacramento State 76, Southern Utah 68
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- DaShawn Freeman scored 17 points and Jason Harris added 12 to lead visiting Sacramento State to a 76-68 win over Southern Utah Saturday. Clark Woods scored 14 points and Justin Williams added 10 for the Hornets (7-4), who have won six of their last eight games. Lubor Olsovsky led Southern Utah (1-8) with 13 points, while Justin Allen had 12 and Fernando Bonfirm scored 11. Steve Barnes and Nate Janes added 10 points each. Sacramento State outshot the Thunderbirds from 3-point range and from the foul line in picking up its second-ever win in Cedar City. The Hornets went 11-28 behind the 3-point line, compared to Southern Utah's 4-16, and made 15 of 18 free throws, compared to the T-Birds' 10 of 19. Trailing 37-28 at the half, Southern Utah cut the lead to a basket five minutes into second half, as Olsovsky fueled a 13-6 run with two layups and a jumper. Allen was fouled while tipping in a missed shot, and his free throw made it 43-41 with 14:41 remaining. Sacramento State scored the next four baskets, including a 3-pointer by Woods, and a dunk and a turnaround jumper by Williams. That gave the Hornets their biggest lead, 52-41. Esteban Bonzano responded with Southern Utah's first 3-pointer, igniting a 19-5 run that gave the Thunderbirds a 60-57 lead with 6:25 left. Sacramento State regained the lead for good on layups by Alex Bausley, Freeman and Williams. Freeman hit consecutive 3-pointers within 40 seconds, putting Sacramento State ahead 69-63 with 2:54 to play. Southern Utah tried to get back into it by fouling, but the Hornets made seven of eight free throws in the final 30 seconds.
